  "title": "Meta Q1 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2025-04-30T20:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q1",
  "location": "Menlo Park, CA",
  "url": "https://investor.fb.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "mark-zuckerberg",
      "speaker_name": "Mark Zuckerberg",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "Q1 2025 was a great quarter. Revenue grew 16% to $42.3 billion. Meta AI reached 1 billion monthly active users in March — the fastest any AI assistant has ever reached that milestone. Llama 4 is the most capable open-weight model available today across reasoning and coding benchmarks. We are committing $60–65 billion in capital expenditures for 2025 to build AI infrastructure that will power the next decade of growth. Threads reached 350 million monthly active users."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "susan-li",
      "speaker_name": "Susan Li",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "Total revenue was $42.3 billion, up 16%, driven by a 14% increase in average price per ad and a 6% increase in ad impressions. Operating income was $17.6 billion with a margin of 41.6%. We generated $13.1 billion in free cash flow. For Q2 2025, we are guiding revenue of $42.5–45.5 billion."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:36:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Eric Sheridan at Goldman Sachs."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-eric-sheridan",
      "speaker_name": "Eric Sheridan",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:36:20",
      "text": "Mark, Meta AI at 1 billion monthly actives is remarkable. Can you share the monetization roadmap — when does it become a meaningful revenue contributor relative to core advertising?"
    }
  ],
